			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Il y a de ces jours dont on sait immédiatement que l&#8217;on va avoir le sourire. Et parfois, ca prend juste un bon café et <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2007/08/27/washington/27cnd-gonzales.html?ex=1345867200&#038;en=2c4fbb59a4107ae9&#038;ei=5088&#038;partner=rssnyt&#038;emc=rss">une nième démission</a>. A ce rythme, les seuls à &#8220;ne pas se souvenir&#8221; de quoi que ce soit d&#8217;ici la fin de l&#8217;année seront le roi et son fou, Georges et Dick&#8230;</p>
<blockquote class="eng" xml:lang="en"><p>
Some days are just bound to be a little more cheerful than others. And sometimes all it takes is a coffee and <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2007/08/27/washington/27cnd-gonzales.html?ex=1345867200&#038;en=2c4fbb59a4107ae9&#038;ei=5088&#038;partner=rssnyt&#038;emc=rss">yet another resignation</a>. At that pace, by the end of the year, the only ones &#8220;not to recall&#8221; anything in this administration will be the king and his buffoon, Georges and Dick&#8230;
</p></blockquote>
